{"author":{"id":"7c138b205f262f086b8af1873d652338045128e756c3d8e7059b60c91cb80ac1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1535448087,"nonce":"aTL8xjTFWhxkHfthSjkpoT4CNW4=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNjUxMzE4Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/coderefinery/documentation/issues/50#issuecomment-416513183"},"message":"I did notice that people were confused about and spending time on the forking and PR, simply because they were doing it for the second time in their life. I absolutely did like how you presented the lesson, but I'm still not convinced it's better than starting from scratch. Most people will be starting from scratch for their own projects, and the \"aha\" moment I would like them to have is to see how easy it is to get a working project/documentation webpage starting from zero. It does take 5 minutes to go through the `sphinx-quickstart`, but the webpage still goes live really quickly. The setting up of RTD account and the GitHub-syncing is similar to what we do in the automated testing lesson and while it does take a little time, it has the effect of lowering the barrier for the learners to start adopting this workflow.\nBut of course I'm all for a continued discussion on this","files":null}]}